9.11.24  2:02 am   What if a lot of the things that people blame on capitalism was actually feudalism's fault all along? For example, occupational surnames seem to imply that you are your job, but they date back to the Middle Ages. Meanwhile, due to the Industrial Revolution making labor more efficient, people have more free time, and they get to have a "work-life balance" with "hobbies". Not everyone works on a farm because not everyone needs to work on a farm. People aren't separated into castes like lords, vassals, and peasants; they can change how much money they earn. Don't get me wrong; the poor get poorer and never any richer, and you are not the car you drive or the contents of your wallet and all that. But I think some clarity on the issue of capitalism is much needed. Thoughts?

      the hypnotic quality of the word capitalism is that i seem to understand less and less what it means, each time the word is used

9.10.24  9:13 pm   Is your website's design simple because of creative choice, ease of maintenance, personal branding, or some combination of all or none of these?

      not even close. it's what i find to be unequivocally the most compelling user experience. it gives you the feeling that you are discovering the website, rather than the website just trying to discover you. but maybe the most powerful thing is this: because the website makes no tangible effort to pull you in or tell you what to do, that means that everyone who's here are people who really want to be here, driven by their own curiosity
